## User experience

### Default behavior
- Watch face displayed at all times, dimly lit
- Hands move smoothly to current time
- Battery indicator shows in a small corner of the face
- No other information is shown by default

### Raise-to-wake
- MPU6050 detects the wrist-raise motion
- Display brightens to full brightness for 5 seconds
- Returns to dim afterward

### Tap (piezo) to cycle info screens
- Tap once: Heart rate (large bpm number, "Steady and healthy" caption)
- Tap twice: Steps today (large number, "of 3,000 goal")
- Tap three times: SpO2 (oxygen %), elevation, etc.
- 5 seconds later: returns to watch face automatically

### Button press
- BTN1 short press: cycle info screens (same as tap)
- BTN1 long press (3s): sleep / power off
- BTN2 short press: confirm/dismiss
- BTN2 long press (3s): SOS escalation

### Choose your face
- App: Settings → Watch face
- Preview gallery of available faces
- Tap to set
- Selection syncs to watch via BLE
- Effective immediately

