## Open questions

1. **Always-on display battery cost** — how much does a dim 10% backlight running 24/7 cost in mAh? Need to test on actual hardware. Apple Watch SE2 with always-on uses ~5% battery per hour. Our display is smaller, but our battery is also smaller (1000mAh).

2. **MPU raise-to-wake reliability** — the algorithm needs tuning. Too sensitive and it wakes up constantly. Not sensitive enough and the user has to shake their wrist. Apple has spent millions on this; we will iterate.

3. **Tap detection latency via piezo** — the piezo signal is fast, but the firmware needs to debounce. Goal is sub-200ms response from tap to screen change. Will test on real hardware.

4. **Face design ownership** — if we use commissioned art, we need licensing. If we use user-uploaded art, we need ToS that says they own the rights.

5. **Sport face vs Classic for v6 default** — currently leaning Classic as default. Could be a setup-time choice during first-run.

